roup presides over meetings of the group and conducts the groups business in an orderly fashion.";i:14;s:164:"There is basically no difference between the words chairman and chairperson and they only refer to the fact that the person occupying the chair is a man or a woman.";i:15;s:110:"It is better to use the word chairperson if you are not aware of the gender of the person occupying the chair.";i:16;s:100:"Traditionally the word chairman was used irrespective of whether the incumbent was a man or a woman.";i:17;s:140:"But over the last few decades many people have tried to avoid words which include the morpheme man because they are seen as excluding women.";i:18;s:83:"Two of the solutions which have been applied to chairman are chairperson and chair.";i:19;s:54:"Both are now in wide use probably chair more commonly.";i:20;s:184:"A committee chair must carefully plan an agenda and send it out to the committee members in sufficient time for committee members to attend the meeting and to participate thoughtfully.";i:21;s:171:"Careful preparation on the committee chairs part will streamline the committees work as they conduct investigations and perform research on the issues they need to tackle.";i:22;s:152:"The chairmanship of the Committee of Ministers is held for a six-month term in turn by the representatives of the members in English alphabetical order.";i:23;s:189:"The chairmanship is transferred from one member State to the next in mid-May and mid-November at a date fixed by the Committee based on a joint proposal by the incoming and outgoing Chairs.";i:24;s:120:"Chairmanship synonyms chairmanship pronunciation chairmanship translation English dictionary definition of chairmanship.";i:25;s:33:"The office or term of a chairman.";i:26;s:29:"German Chair and Vice-Chairs.";i:27;s:49:"Chairs up from 23 at the beginning of the decade.";i:28;s:78:"Of the 40 19 may be classified as independent Chairs up from 9 five years ago.";i:29;s:199:"Booz Allens research on CEO succession reports that in the US only 165 of incoming 2009 CEOs had both the CEO and Chair title a much lower number than 2000 when about half the incoming CEOs occupied.";i:30;s:164:"The Chairmanship consists of the chair and vice chair of the Board of Directors both of whom are elected directly by the shareholders at the Annual General Meeting.";i:31;s:157:"At the Annual General Meeting in March 2021 Helge Lund was re-elected as chair and Jeppe Christiansen was re-elected as vice chair of the Board of Directors.";i:32;s:89:"Helge Lund became chair of the Board in 2018 and Jeppe Christiansen became vice chair in.";i:33;s:39:"Russian Federation vice chair Botswana.";i:34;s:41:"No chairmanship due to Covid-19 pandemic.";i:35;s:36:"India vice chair Russian Federation.";i:36;s:32:"European Union vice chair India.";i:37;s:251:"Russias two-year chairmanship period will include as many as 88 events of which 50 will be officially organized by the chair and the remaining 38 will be unofficial held under there auspices of the Council Presidential Adviser Anton Kobyakov confirms.";i:38;s:86:"The 50 official events will alone have 12500 participants he said in a recent meeting.";i:39;s:248:"The Committee on Participation and Chairmanship assists the Chair of the Kimberley Process in handling the admission of new participants and advises if a Participant fails to comply with requirements which can lead to their removal from the scheme.";i:40;s:71:"It also reviews and assesses candidates for the position of Vice-Chair.";i:41;s:40:"Thailands Chairmanship of ASEAN in 2019.";i:42;s:39:"- by Don Pramudwinai - Leave a Comment.";i:43;s:228:"As Thailand assumes the Chair of ASEAN for the year 2019 we cannot help but look back with pride at the accomplishments of this remarkable and resilient regional grouping ever since its founding in Bangkok over five decades ago.";i:44;s:81:"The terms Vice chairmanship and Vice chair might have synonymous similar meaning.";i:45;s:42:"Find out what connects these two synonyms.";i:46;s:67:"Understand the difference between Vice chairmanship and Vice chair.";i:47;s:59:"Terms with meaning between hold the chairmanship and chair.";i:48;s:53:"Use side links for further pursuit of a perfect term.";i:49;s:94:"Preside take the chair assume the presidency assume the chairmanship take over the presidency.";i:50;s:146:"Yassin Al Suroor is the founder and the Executive Chairman of Aamal group he is also board member of various regional and international companies.";i:51;s:136:"He is the chair of Aamal Foundation Chair of Aamal Capital Limited and sits on the executive committee of ICC World Chambers Federation.";i:52;s:29:"German Chair and Vice-Chairs.";}}